<subSubSection id="C37B65219550651A2C80FBFA72C4FB82" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA9550651A2C80FBFA72C4FB82" blockId="1.[178,1085,1085,1136]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562">Etymology: The specific epithet is the past participle of the Latin verb depravare (to deform) and alludes to the distinctly asymmetric male sternite VIII.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37B6521955065182C80FBB87022FDB0" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1564" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA9550651A2C80FBB870F5FB22" blockId="1.[178,1086,1151,1232]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562">
Description: Body length 7.5-9.0 mm; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4C999B4F9550651A2F58FBB872A7FB67" box="[874,995,1151,1173]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562" unit="mm" value="3.0999999999999996" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="2.8">2.8-3.4 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="135A2A2F9550651A2CDEFB5A706FFB41" box="[236,299,1181,1203]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[178,218,1513,1533]" captionTargetBox="[187,1084,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-48@2.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5: Oedichirus depravatus nov.sp.: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) aedeagus in lateral view; (5) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 3- 5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302819/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Coloration: body reddish, with abdominal segments VII-X black; legs and antennae dark-yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA9550651A2C80FB187265FA98" blockId="1.[178,1085,1247,1386]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562">
Head (
<figureCitation id="135A2A2F9550651A2CC4FB187077FB07" box="[246,307,1247,1269]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[178,218,1513,1533]" captionTargetBox="[187,1084,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-48@2.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5: Oedichirus depravatus nov.sp.: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) aedeagus in lateral view; (5) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 3- 5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302819/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) transverse, approximately 1.2 times as broad as long, broadest across eyes; posterior angles sharply marked by a small setiferous projection; dorsal surface with few coarse punctures, the median ones arranged in a transverse oval or rectangle, near posterior margin with a transverse row of densely set punctures. Eyes strongly convex, almost reaching posterior margin of head. Antenna 
<quantity id="4C999B4F9550651A2E40FA9373A3FA98" box="[626,743,1364,1386]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562" unit="mm" value="2.3" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.2">2.2-2.4 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA9550651A2C80FABD705FF9F6" blockId="1.[178,1086,1402,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="135A2A2F9550651A2D14FABD7021FA62" box="[294,357,1402,1424]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[178,218,1513,1533]" captionTargetBox="[187,1084,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-48@2.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5: Oedichirus depravatus nov.sp.: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) aedeagus in lateral view; (5) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 3- 5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302819/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1562">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.1 times as long as broad and 1.1 times as broad as head, widest in anterior half and distinctly tapering posteriorly; punctation very coarse, coarser than that of head, somewhat irregularly spaced in anterior third and forming a dorsal series of 4-5 punctures on either side of middle in posterior two thirds of pronotum.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1E6622955365192C80FA2E7052F9D8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302819" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5302819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302819/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563" startId="2.[178,218,1513,1533]" targetBox="[187,1084,212,1480]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA955365192C80FA2E7052F9D8" blockId="2.[178,1085,1513,1578]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563">
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955365192C80FA2E7047FA0F" bold="true" box="[178,259,1513,1533]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563">Figs 1-5</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D29955365192D26FA2E70ACFA0F" authority="Assing, 2013" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[276,488,1513,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oedichirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depravatus" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955365192D26FA2E70ACFA0F" box="[276,488,1513,1533]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563">Oedichirus depravatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22657C3955365192DC0FA2E737CFA0F" box="[498,568,1513,1533]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: (
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955365192E7EFA2E7313FA0F" bold="true" box="[588,599,1513,1533]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563">1</emphasis>
) habitus; (
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955365192EF1FA2E738AFA0F" bold="true" box="[707,718,1513,1533]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563">2</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955365192F78FA2E7211FA0F" bold="true" box="[842,853,1513,1533]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563">3</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955365192818FA2E7571FA0F" bold="true" box="[1066,1077,1513,1533]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563">4</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral view; (
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955365192D93FA3870E8F9E1" bold="true" box="[417,428,1535,1555]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1563">5</emphasis>
) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 3- 5: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA955265182C80FF1D704DFED9" blockId="3.[178,1085,218,299]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="135A2A2F955265182D32FF1D707AFF02" box="[256,318,218,240]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[178,218,1513,1533]" captionTargetBox="[187,1084,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-48@2.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5: Oedichirus depravatus nov.sp.: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) aedeagus in lateral view; (5) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 3- 5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302819/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) short, approximately 0.65 times as long as pronotum, widest in posterior half; humeral angles completely obsolete; punctation very coarse. Hind wings completely reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA955265182C80FEFD71B2FE11" blockId="3.[178,1085,314,483]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">Abdomen approximately as broad as elytra; anterior impression of tergite III with normal punctation, impressions of tergites IV-VI with numerous longitudinal keels separated by small impressions; remainder of tergal surfaces with coarse punctures arranged in two (tergite III) or three (tergites IV-VII) transverse rows; punctures on tergite VII distinctly less coarse than those on tergites III-VI; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA955265182CF5FE347022FDB0" blockId="3.[178,1085,498,578]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">
: sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="135A2A2F955265182D51FE3570E5FDFA" box="[355,417,498,520]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[178,218,1513,1533]" captionTargetBox="[187,1084,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-48@2.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5: Oedichirus depravatus nov.sp.: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) aedeagus in lateral view; (5) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 3- 5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302819/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) with distinctly asymmetric posterior excision, this excision furnished with modified stout yellowish setae; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="135A2A2F955265182ED0FDC8727EFDD7" box="[738,826,527,549]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[178,218,1513,1533]" captionTargetBox="[187,1084,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-48@2.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5: Oedichirus depravatus nov.sp.: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) aedeagus in lateral view; (5) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 3- 5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302819/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">Figs 4-5</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4C999B4F955265182F7BFDC872D3FDD7" box="[841,919,527,549]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long and somewhat asymmetric.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37B6521955265182C80FD95708EFD08" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA955265182C80FD95708EFD08" blockId="3.[178,1085,594,762]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">
Comparative notes: Using the key in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF04B5B955265182EECFD9572D3FD9A" author="CAMERON M" box="[734,919,594,616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" refId="ref3243" refString="CAMERON M. (1931): The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Coleoptera. Staphylinidae. Volume 2. - London, Taylor and Francis: viii + 257 pp." type="book" year="1931">CAMERON (1931)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D29955265182F9AFD957579FD9A" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[936,1085,594,616]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oedichirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depravatus">
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955265182F9AFD957579FD9A" box="[936,1085,594,616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">O. depravatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would key out at couplet 6, together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D29955265182E6BFDB772F8FD77" authority="BERNHAUER 1902" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1902" box="[601,956,623,645]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oedichirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufotestaceus">
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955265182E6BFDB773BBFD77" box="[601,767,623,645]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">O. rufotestaceus</emphasis>
BERNHAUER 1902
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="F376763A955265182FFBFDA87576FD77" box="[969,1074,623,645]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
), from which it differs by larger size (
<taxonomicName id="4C614D29955265182E16FD4A738EFD50" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1902" box="[548,714,652,674]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oedichirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufotestaceus">
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955265182E16FD4A738EFD50" box="[548,714,652,674]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">O. rufotestaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<quantity id="4C999B4F955265182EEAFD4A7257FD50" box="[728,787,653,674]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
) and by the different punctation of the pronotum and of the elytra (
<taxonomicName id="4C614D29955265182E7AFD6D73ABFD32" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1902" box="[584,751,682,704]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oedichirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufotestaceus">
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955265182E7AFD6D73ABFD32" box="[584,751,682,704]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">O. rufotestaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: pronotum with fine punctation; elytral punctation arranged in distinct rows). The male sexual characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D29955265182816FD0F707DFD08" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oedichirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufotestaceus">
<emphasis id="B915EAB8955265182816FD0F707DFD08" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">O. rufotestaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37B6521955265182C80FCCE70A4FCA8" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BDE36AA955265182C80FCCE70A4FCA8" blockId="3.[178,1085,777,858]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">
Distribution and natural history: The 
<typeStatus id="54DA8808955265182F69FCCD723BFCED" box="[859,895,778,799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected in two geographically close localities in 
<collectingRegion id="49A5F848955265182E89FCE0726AFCCF" box="[699,814,807,829]" country="India" name="Meghalaya" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">Meghalaya</collectingRegion>
, Northeast 
<collectingCountry id="F376763A955265182F94FCE0729EFCCF" box="[934,986,807,829]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">India</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="135A2A2F955265182FDBFCE07569FCCF" box="[1001,1069,807,829]" captionStart="Map 1" captionStartId="5.[178,223,1052,1072]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1026]" captionTargetId="figure-164@5.[178,1085,212,1026]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Map 1: Distributions of Oedichirus depravatus nov.sp. (triangles), O. bicuspidatus nov.sp. (circle), and Paederus borailicus nov.sp. (circle)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302823/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564">Map 1</figureCitation>
), at altitudes of 450 and 
<specimenCount id="9D67FD23955265182DABFC8370A4FCA8" box="[409,480,836,858]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" type="generic">
<quantity id="4C999B4F955265182DABFC837098FCA8" box="[409,476,836,858]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="1564" unit="m" value="800.0">800 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
